This paper discusses the optimization of data processing in big data frameworks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) since the paper focuses on data-parallel computing frameworks and distributed memory. The second likely category is cs.DB (Databases) since the paper discusses caching decisions and intermediate datasets. The third likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) since the paper mentions the performance improvement of machine learning applications. The fourth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper proposes an algorithm for caching decisions. The fifth likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering) since the paper discusses the automation of caching decisions and optimization of total work.
